KANO – Professor Hafizu Abubakar, the former Deputy Governor of Kano state on Saturday drove a wedge on the electoral fortune of Ganduje’s anointed candidates, Nasiru Gawuna, and his running mate, Sule Garo as he described the duo as candidate of Correctional centre. Professor Abubakar who spoke in Kano during Malam Aminu Kano memorial lecture that held at center for Democratic Research and Training Mambayya House Kano said the antecedents of the two top political actor stand between them and the top job. Professor Hafiz Abubakar was Deputy to Ganduje between 2015 – 2018 before he resigned over irreconcilable differences with his boss. -Advertisement- The Professor of Health Nutrition said “in a civilised society, the anointed candidates of the ruling All Progressives Congress in Kano state are supposed to be in jail.” Professor Hafizu Abubakar who x-rayed the infamous role played by the two top runners in a series of event events that led to the disruption of 2019 election in Kano, and the subsequent run off described as unfortunate the decision to reward them as candidates of the ruling party. Hafiz said “We saw the two candidates during the 2019 Gubernatorial election in Kano disrupting the collation process and snatching ballot boxes, yet this the best we could offer.” He noted that “the world is a witness on how the acts perpetrated by the two candidates were witnessed all over the world and their reward now is getting Gubernatorial ticket of the APC.” He noted that the world is a witness on how the acts perpetrated by the two candidates were witnessed all over the world and their reward now is getting Gubernatorial ticket of the APC. POLL Professor Hafizu Abubakar said the Kano APC anointed aspirants played a crucial role in ensuring inconclusive election.